<br>
When symbol was first introduced it was done so as a raid buff and given a prohibitively expensive cost that only guilds raiding PoH/PoG (then end game zones) would have enough gems to cover the cost given kill speeds of the day.<br>
<br>
However symbols became the standard for group play, and whilst that is the case and I cannot see any change in the use of symbol without a serious game overhaul, I think the prohibitive cost may aswell be done away with.  What does it contribute to the gameplay to give a regent cost to symbol spells?<br>
<br>
As I said before I more or less dont care about regent costs.  I just go cash farming from time to time and most of the time I am moderately rich with a 5 digit bank account, but i've played through rough finances in EQ before [and infact am broke atm], i've been reduced to cash farming greens in my younger levels because I ran out of dots and cash.<br>
<br>
There really isn't any justification for burdening 1 member of the group with an expensive regent spell.  Sure some groups compensate the cleric, some groups even over-compensate, but some groups dont.<br>
<br>
Why do we even have this issue?<br>
<br>
I am at a stage where I dont much care about regent costs, but I do think EQ would be a better game if they where removed completely.  They are for most regent-based spells completely unecessary.<br>
<br>
Why should a mage have to have a pearl on them to CoH?  The cost is insignificant.  It's just an inventory slot used up and it's annoying when you run out.  It adds nothing to gameplay.<br>
<br>
Why should SK pets require a bone chip?  It meens that you have to take the skeletons away from the newbies for half an hour every now and then.  It's a waste of half an hour, and it's derrogatory to the gameplay of others.<br>
<br>
Why should chanters without AA have to pay for Rune.  I've met some of the clerics out they that they are defending themselves against, is it their fault that many clerics are incompetant twats?  Why should they pay for the defficiencies of others?<br>
